title: $564K+ Bankers Trust Company Settlement Ends Class Action Lawsuit Over Alleged Overdraft Fees
description: A $564K+ Bankers Trust Company settlement offers cash and debt forgiveness to individuals who were charged overdraft fees on debit card transactions.

title: Paramount Lawsuit Claims Pluto TV Harvests Personal Info from Videos Watched by Children
description: A class action lawsuit says that Paramount unlawfully harvests and discloses the private info of minors to third parties like Google and Microsoft.

title: Black Rifle Lawsuit Claims ‘America’s Coffee’ Not Produced in the United States As Advertised
description: A class action lawsuit claims that Black Rifle coffee products are not made entirely in the United States.

title: $1.3M CarePro Health Services Settlement Ends Class Action Suit Over November 2023 Data Breach
description: A $1.3M CarePro Health Services class action settlement offers cash and credit monitoring to patients impacted by a Nov. 2023 data breach.

title: ZYN Lawsuit Claims Pouches Are Falsely Advertised as Tobacco-Free, Low-Nicotine
description: The makers of ZYN pouches face a lawsuit over their advertising of the items as “tobacco-free,” and label claims concerning the grams of nicotine in each pouch.
